## Powershell Introduction:
It is task automation framework build on .Net framework to provide a uniform command line experience to administrators and other folks who wants to control and configure the system.

Powershell commands provide Verb-noun syntax.

Examples:
- get-process
- start-process
- get-Content
- start-process

Its a uniform method to access registry, environment variabbles, or drives. Get-psdrive whould list the read and virtual drives which powershell uses. 

Powershell Command types:

Alias
Cmdlet
Functions
Scripts
Executable or Binary which are present in PATH

Pipelining in powershell is a concept to sent the output of a cmdlet/function to another set of cmdlet/function using |. Unlike unix the data passed in pipe are objects rather then text.

